WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
If you have your Bible with you this morning, 2 Corinthians chapter number 11.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:11.000
I didn't have an opportunity to preach last week, Brother Dan Hummel was here, but two weeks ago

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.000
on Sunday morning we looked at the first 15 verses of 2 Corinthians chapter number 11.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:21.000
And this morning we'll look at verses 16 down through verse number 33

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.000
here in 2 Corinthians chapter number 11.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
I want to remind you as we look at this text of Scripture

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
that the Apostle Paul started in verse number 1 of this text,

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:35.000
and again it was a couple of weeks ago that I looked at this passage.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:42.000
But he says, Would to God ye could bear with me a little in my folly, and indeed bear with me.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:46.000
We find that the Apostle Paul begins the chapter writing this way

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:52.000
because of really the atmosphere there in Corinth with regard to the false teachers,

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:55.000
these Judaizers and all that was going on.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:59.000
They could be described as, and we'll look at it as we get further into the message this morning,

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:01.000
really as being boasters.

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:09.000
And so the Apostle Paul is really put in a position in which they're asking and they're requiring,

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:14.000
if you're really an apostle, then what is the evidence, if you will.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.000
And the Apostle Paul says, Bear with me a little in my folly.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:22.000
And really he's speaking with a measure of sarcasm as you go through the text.

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:28.000
And he's beginning to help these people understand what God had called him to,

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:33.000
but also if you want me to kind of come to this level of these Judaizers,

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:35.000
here's what I'll share with you.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:39.000
But it's really fascinating as you get through the entirety of the text

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:46.000
and really see how the Apostle Paul is going to present the work of the ministry,

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:52.000
what God has called him to do, what God has enabled him to do, all for the glory of God.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:02:00.000
And really we are reminded that our lives are to be spent to bring honor and glory to the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:06.000
Whether therefore you eat or drink or whatsoever you do, do all to the glory of God.

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:09.000
And he had written that to this church.

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:14.000
In 1 Corinthians, we find that he wrote that truth to the church in Corinth

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:19.000
and they needed to understand that all that we are is because of the grace of God

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:23.000
and all that we do is for the glory of God.

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:27.000
So we begin looking at the passage this morning beginning in verse number 16.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:29.000
And notice the Bible says this,

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:35.000
I say again, let no man think me a fool, if otherwise yet as a fool receive me,

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:38.000
that I may boast myself a little.

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:41.000
That which I speak, I speak it not after the Lord,

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:45.000
but as it were foolishly in this confidence of boasting,

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:49.000
seeing that many glory after the flesh, I will glory also.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:53.000
For you suffer fools gladly, seeing ye yourselves are wise.

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:58.000
For you suffer if a man bring you into bondage, if a man devour you, if a man take of you,

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:03.000
if a man exalt himself, if a man smite you on the face.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:08.000
Verse 21, I speak as concerning reproach, as though we had been weak,

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:14.000
albeit whereinsoever, and he is bold, I speak foolishly, I am bold also.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:17.000
As we read that introduction this morning and we'll get through the end of the chapter,

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:19.000
you could say, what in the world is going on?

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:22.000
Why is Paul speaking the way that he's speaking?

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:26.000
And again, it's because of this climate that's taking place here,

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:28.000
the environment there in Corinth.

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
And Paul knew that if anyone were to glory, they're to glory in the Lord.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:34.000
He knew that, he had written that,

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:38.000
he understood that he says that no flesh should glory in his presence.

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:42.000
If you read 1 Corinthians 1, it's very plain and understood.

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:46.000
Not only did Paul write that under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God,

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:52.000
Paul knew that, he knew that all that he was to do was for the glory of God.

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:55.000
But he's coming to this place where some are saying,

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:59.000
well, look at these guys and what about you, Paul?

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:00.000
What about you, Paul?

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:05.000
And Paul says, this is what he says here, he says in verse number 16,

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:09.000
if otherwise yet as a fool receive me that I may boast myself a little.

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:13.000
And in this confidence boasting, verse 18,

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:17.000
seeing that many glory after the flesh, I will glory also.

00:04:17.000 --> 00:04:20.000
And understand that as Paul is speaking these things,

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:26.000
he's really bringing himself to a level based upon the request

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:30.000
or the requirement, if you will, of the body there in Corinth.

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:33.000
And it's important for us to understand that at the onset

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:35.000
as we enter into the message this morning,

00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:40.000
because otherwise we will not be able to gain a proper understanding

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:42.000
of this portion of scripture.

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:45.000
These false teachers that were present there in Corinth, they were boasters.

00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:49.000
It's interesting to me that if you read 2 Timothy chapter number 3,

00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:53.000
that is the apostle Paul is writing to his son in the faith, Timothy,

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:57.000
about the last days and describing the last days.

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:01.000
That is one of the terms that is used, boasters.

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:05.000
And these boasters as they were, these Judaizers here in Corinth,

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:09.000
they were saying, hey, look at us, look at me, look at what,

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:11.000
and you find that's all pride.

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:13.000
It's all pride.

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:16.000
And they're trying to make a name for themselves.

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
I said this to you a few weeks ago as we looked at this,

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:22.000
or a couple of weeks ago,

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:26.000
that the apostle Paul was using his office, his position,

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:29.000
to build up the church,

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:34.000
but the Judaizers were using the church to build up their position.

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:37.000
And there's a great difference in that.

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:40.000
And so the apostle Paul is left with this crazy climate,

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:42.000
the mood, if you will, in Corinth,

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:45.000
and it resulted in the text of scripture that we have here before us.

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:48.000
But as you study the text, here's the amazing thing,

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:50.000
and I'll give you kind of the upfront,

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:53.000
what we're going to find as we get through it this morning.

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:55.000
But what you find and what you will note,

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:58.000
that even in his quote-unquote boasting,

00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:02.000
he is actually exalting his Savior, the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:06.000
It's actually pretty awesome how the apostle Paul will write this

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:09.000
and will give what they're asking for,

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:15.000
but in so doing, ensuring that Jesus is glorified.

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:19.000
And that's so imperative and important for us to understand

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:21.000
that it's all about Jesus.

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:23.000
Remember what John the Baptist said,

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:26.000
he must increase, I must decrease.

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:28.000
It's all about Jesus, amen?

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
And we understand that we're seeking to point people to Jesus,

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:34.000
to be followers of Jesus.

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:36.000
And what a blessing.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:39.000
The apostle Paul, as I read this text of scripture,

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:41.000
and we see what's taking place,

00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:43.000
and what Paul begins to explain,

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:46.000
I am reminded of a declaration that Paul made

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:50.000
as he's writing to the church in Philippi.

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:52.000
In Philippians chapter 3 and verse number 10,

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:54.000
Paul says this,

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:56.000
that I may know him,

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:59.000
and the power of his resurrection,

00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:02.000
and the fellowship of his sufferings,

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:07.000
being made conformable unto his death.

00:07:07.000 --> 00:07:10.000
As I look at that verse in Philippians 3 and verse number 10,

00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:12.000
I often consider that first phrase,

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:14.000
that I may know him.

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:16.000
And how important it is that we know God.

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:20.000
How important it is that we know intimately the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:22.000
And how do we know him?

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:24.000
We know him through his word.

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:28.000
God reveals himself to us, to humanity, through his word.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:31.000
Yes, the heavens declare the glory of God,

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:35.000
but without a Bible, you can't know all of who God is.

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:38.000
And I'm thankful that we have a Bible this morning,

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:40.000
and I'm thankful that I can know him.

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:43.000
And then I think about this, and the power of his resurrection.

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:46.000
And I'm so thankful that we serve a risen Savior, that he lives.

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:49.000
In fact, one of the songs I think that we're singing tonight,

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:52.000
he lives, and what a great song it is.

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:56.000
Listen, I'm thankful that I don't serve a dead God, a dead deity.

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:00.000
My God lives, he reigns, he rules, he's coming back.

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:02.000
Praise God, amen?

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:05.000
I mean, we have hope, and we have joy. Why?

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:09.000
Because we serve a risen Savior, the power of his resurrection.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:12.000
There's no one like Jesus, amen?

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:14.000
And what a joy.

00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:16.000
But then we read that he says,

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:20.000
and the fellowship of his sufferings.

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:24.000
You know, there was great suffering before there was a resurrection.

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:27.000
Great suffering before there's a resurrection.

00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:31.000
Peter talks about being eyewitnesses of his sufferings.

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:36.000
If you read 1 Peter 5, you'll read as Peter is addressing

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:39.000
and writing to a group of believers

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:41.000
that are suffering persecution,

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:45.000
that are suffering great trial and difficulty.

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:49.000
And he speaks in the last chapter about the sufferings of Christ.

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:52.000
But then comes the glory. Hallelujah.

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:55.000
There's glory, but after the suffering.

00:08:55.000 --> 00:09:00.000
And he says this being made conformable unto his death.

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:05.000
I'm thankful that the Lord Jesus Christ as good shepherd

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:08.000
gave his life for the sheep.

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:11.000
I'm thankful that he was willing to go to that cruel cross

00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:13.000
to suffer, to bleed, and to die

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:16.000
for your sin and for my sin and the sin of the world.

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:19.000
And he rose, conquering sin, death, and the grave.

00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:22.000
But this morning as I look at this passage of Scripture

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:25.000
in 2 Corinthians 11, that phrase

00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:28.000
from in the midst of Philippians 3 and verse 10

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:32.000
resonates in my mind, the fellowship of his sufferings.

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:35.000
That's why I titled the message this morning

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:37.000
The Fellowship of His Sufferings.

00:09:37.000 --> 00:09:39.000
Consider with me as we make our way

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:41.000
through this text of Scripture,

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:43.000
number one, consider the trials.

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:45.000
Paul gives the introduction as I read it

00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:47.000
in verses 16 through 21.

00:09:47.000 --> 00:09:51.000
And he begins in verse 22, down through verse 29,

00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:54.000
detailing the trials that are given.

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:56.000
In verse 22, the Bible says,

00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:58.000
Are they Hebrews? So am I.

00:09:58.000 --> 00:10:00.000
Are they Israelites? So am I.

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:02.839
Are they the seed of Abraham? So am I.

00:10:02.839 --> 00:10:06.840
Are they ministers of Christ? I speak as a fool. I am more."

00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:08.300
Notice in verse 23,

00:10:08.300 --> 00:10:11.180
"...in labors more abundant,

00:10:11.180 --> 00:10:13.560
in stripes above measure,

00:10:13.560 --> 00:10:16.180
in prisons more frequent,

00:10:16.180 --> 00:10:18.260
in deaths oft."

00:10:18.260 --> 00:10:19.979
We'll continue reading in just a moment,

00:10:19.979 --> 00:10:21.180
but as we begin to read,

00:10:21.180 --> 00:10:24.319
as Paul is going to help us to consider the trials,

00:10:24.319 --> 00:10:25.899
I want you to understand this morning

00:10:25.899 --> 00:10:29.399
that trials are to be expected.

00:10:29.440 --> 00:10:31.760
Trials are to be expected.

00:10:31.760 --> 00:10:34.560
Listen, I'm thankful that I'm going to heaven.

00:10:34.560 --> 00:10:36.180
Amen. I am thankful that I'm going to heaven.

00:10:36.180 --> 00:10:38.599
I'm thankful this world is not my home.

00:10:38.599 --> 00:10:42.319
I am thankful that I have the promise

00:10:42.319 --> 00:10:46.479
of eternal bliss with my Savior forever and ever.

00:10:46.479 --> 00:10:48.740
But I understand,

00:10:48.740 --> 00:10:51.119
and it's important for every believer to understand

00:10:51.119 --> 00:10:53.459
that while we walk upon this earth,

00:10:53.459 --> 00:10:56.040
we will have trials.

00:10:56.040 --> 00:10:58.299
Trials are to be expected.

00:10:58.319 --> 00:11:01.319
We find that the Apostle Paul was aware of this.

00:11:01.319 --> 00:11:02.319
If you hold your place here

00:11:02.319 --> 00:11:04.860
and turn back to the book of Acts, if you will.

00:11:04.860 --> 00:11:07.239
And I want you to notice in Acts chapter number nine,

00:11:07.239 --> 00:11:09.319
and we'll look at two passages very quickly

00:11:09.319 --> 00:11:11.580
in the book of Acts to help us understand

00:11:11.580 --> 00:11:13.500
that trials are to be expected.

00:11:13.500 --> 00:11:16.239
The Apostle Paul begins to explain these trials

00:11:16.239 --> 00:11:20.080
as he is going to speak to these believers in Corinth,

00:11:20.080 --> 00:11:22.839
and of course for us by way of preservation.

00:11:22.839 --> 00:11:27.839
But we understand that after Paul was saved there in Acts 9,

00:11:27.839 --> 00:11:31.540
notice what the Bible says in verses 15 and 16

00:11:31.540 --> 00:11:35.660
with regard to this fact that trials are to be expected.

00:11:35.660 --> 00:11:39.180
In verse number 15, remember the Lord Jesus Christ

00:11:39.180 --> 00:11:42.599
after Paul, Saul at the time was saved,

00:11:42.599 --> 00:11:45.900
that he appeared to Ananias and gave Ananias

00:11:45.900 --> 00:11:47.620
some piece of instruction,

00:11:47.620 --> 00:11:50.059
and Ananias has some conversation with the Lord.

00:11:50.059 --> 00:11:51.699
And in verse number 15, the Bible says,

00:11:51.699 --> 00:11:55.580
but the Lord said unto him, go thy way.

00:11:55.580 --> 00:11:58.080
So God is speaking to Ananias in verse 15.

00:11:58.080 --> 00:12:01.319
He says, go thy way for he, that's Saul,

00:12:01.319 --> 00:12:02.959
who we know as being Paul,

00:12:02.959 --> 00:12:05.779
for he is a chosen vessel unto me

00:12:05.779 --> 00:12:09.960
to bear my name before the Gentiles and kings

00:12:09.960 --> 00:12:11.639
and the children of Israel.

00:12:11.639 --> 00:12:13.839
The Apostle Paul was gonna have a great ministry

00:12:13.839 --> 00:12:16.100
that as he would give himself,

00:12:16.100 --> 00:12:18.960
as he would surrender his life and his will

00:12:18.960 --> 00:12:21.940
to the will of God, that God would use him

00:12:21.940 --> 00:12:25.039
to not only be a witness amongst the Gentiles,

00:12:25.380 --> 00:12:27.380
but amongst kings, even the children of Israel.

00:12:27.380 --> 00:12:29.500
And you find that as you study the life

00:12:29.500 --> 00:12:32.199
of the Apostle Paul, because he was surrendered,

00:12:32.199 --> 00:12:34.440
because he said, I am crucified with Christ,

00:12:34.440 --> 00:12:37.020
because he said that he wanted to live for the Lord,

00:12:37.020 --> 00:12:40.800
that Paul was used in this manner.

00:12:40.800 --> 00:12:44.259
He spoke before the Gentiles, proclaimed the gospel.

00:12:44.259 --> 00:12:47.259
He stood before kings and preached the gospel.

00:12:47.259 --> 00:12:50.259
He stood before the children of Israel

00:12:50.259 --> 00:12:52.559
and preached the gospel.

00:12:52.559 --> 00:12:54.479
But look at verse 16.

00:12:54.479 --> 00:12:57.720
For I will show him, God says to Ananias,

00:12:57.720 --> 00:13:00.720
for I will show him, Saul, Paul,

00:13:00.720 --> 00:13:05.720
how great things he must suffer for my namesake.

00:13:08.919 --> 00:13:10.520
We find that in chapter number 20,

00:13:10.520 --> 00:13:12.300
notice if you will, in Acts chapter 20,

00:13:12.300 --> 00:13:15.240
we can fast forward from the time of Paul's conversion

00:13:15.240 --> 00:13:18.039
to now as he's gone on these missionary journeys,

00:13:18.039 --> 00:13:19.800
as he's heading back to Jerusalem

00:13:19.800 --> 00:13:22.919
and he's called for the leaders of the church at Ephesus

00:13:22.919 --> 00:13:24.919
to come and to meet with him

00:13:24.919 --> 00:13:29.639
as he's journeying on his way to go to Jerusalem,

00:13:29.639 --> 00:13:32.880
that here in Acts chapter 20 and verse 23,

00:13:32.880 --> 00:13:35.720
the Bible says, I'll read verse 22,

00:13:35.720 --> 00:13:38.160
that Paul says to these leaders of the church,

00:13:38.160 --> 00:13:41.960
now, behold, I go bound in the Spirit unto Jerusalem,

00:13:41.960 --> 00:13:45.119
not knowing the things that shall befall me there,

00:13:45.119 --> 00:13:48.440
save that the Holy Ghost witnesseth in every city,

00:13:48.440 --> 00:13:53.440
saying that bonds and afflictions abide me.

00:13:54.080 --> 00:13:56.600
Yea, all those that live godly in Christ Jesus

00:13:56.600 --> 00:13:58.600
shall suffer persecution.

00:13:58.600 --> 00:14:01.279
We read that as Paul is writing to Timothy,

00:14:01.279 --> 00:14:03.279
and we find this morning that is,

00:14:03.279 --> 00:14:07.119
we understand as Paul is going to give some details

00:14:07.119 --> 00:14:09.199
and he says, consider the trials,

00:14:09.199 --> 00:14:11.000
that it's important for each of us,

00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:13.039
just as it was important in Paul's life

00:14:13.039 --> 00:14:16.720
to understand that trials are to be expected.

00:14:16.720 --> 00:14:19.920
Can I tell you this morning that lost people face trials

00:14:19.920 --> 00:14:22.119
the same way saved people face trials?

00:14:23.160 --> 00:14:24.760
There's a great difference.

00:14:26.160 --> 00:14:28.200
I have Jesus.

00:14:28.200 --> 00:14:33.200
When I face my trial, I don't face it alone, amen?

00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:34.720
When I face my trial,

