00:45:45.499 --> 00:45:48.539
As Paul surrendered and yielded,

00:45:48.539 --> 00:45:49.879
God would continue to use him.

00:45:49.879 --> 00:45:51.659
But you know that there was no one else

00:45:51.659 --> 00:45:54.659
that was gonna cut Paul's ministry short.

00:45:56.299 --> 00:46:00.859
God was gonna use Paul to do what God wanted Paul to do

00:46:00.879 --> 00:46:03.979
as Paul would surrender and yield himself to God.

00:46:04.919 --> 00:46:09.919
And God gave to Paul in this first instance,

00:46:10.079 --> 00:46:12.799
right after he got saved in Acts chapter number nine,

00:46:12.799 --> 00:46:17.679
he miraculously helped him and he enabled him to endure

00:46:17.679 --> 00:46:20.639
for the cause of Christ and for the care of the churches.

00:46:20.639 --> 00:46:22.919
And we find that the apostle Paul,

00:46:22.919 --> 00:46:27.319
he's giving testimony of what God has done.

00:46:28.319 --> 00:46:31.859
As Paul writes and finishes

00:46:31.859 --> 00:46:33.899
in second Timothy chapter number three,

00:46:35.799 --> 00:46:37.979
and then in chapter four, we'll finish with this.

00:46:37.979 --> 00:46:39.819
The Bible says this in second Timothy three

00:46:39.819 --> 00:46:41.219
in verse number 11.

00:46:46.899 --> 00:46:48.779
He says, persecutions, afflictions,

00:46:48.779 --> 00:46:52.359
which came unto me at Antioch, at Iconium, at Lystra.

00:46:52.359 --> 00:46:56.859
What persecutions I endured, but out of them all,

00:46:57.539 --> 00:47:00.039
the Lord delivered me.

00:47:01.579 --> 00:47:06.499
Out of them all, the Lord delivered me.

00:47:06.499 --> 00:47:09.739
He says in chapter four, in verse 17,

00:47:11.259 --> 00:47:14.379
notwithstanding, after he writes about Alexander

00:47:14.379 --> 00:47:15.939
did a much evil about the fact

00:47:15.939 --> 00:47:18.339
that no man stood with him in verse 16.

00:47:18.339 --> 00:47:21.099
He says, notwithstanding, the Lord stood with me

00:47:21.939 --> 00:47:25.059
and strengthened me that by me,

00:47:25.059 --> 00:47:26.939
the preaching might be fully known

00:47:27.479 --> 00:47:29.119
and that all the Gentiles might hear.

00:47:29.119 --> 00:47:33.999
And I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion

00:47:33.999 --> 00:47:37.499
and the Lord shall deliver me from every evil work

00:47:37.499 --> 00:47:40.859
and will preserve me unto his heavenly kingdom

00:47:40.859 --> 00:47:45.719
to whom be glory forever and ever, amen.

00:47:45.719 --> 00:47:47.439
Powerful testimony.

00:47:48.399 --> 00:47:52.539
But the testimony comes after the trial.

00:47:53.519 --> 00:47:58.159
I'm thankful that I can know the Lord.

00:47:58.159 --> 00:48:02.679
I'm thankful to know the power of his resurrection.

00:48:03.959 --> 00:48:05.159
But the verse doesn't end there.

00:48:05.159 --> 00:48:08.959
It says in the fellowship of his sufferings,

00:48:08.959 --> 00:48:12.719
being made conformable unto his death.

00:48:12.719 --> 00:48:17.079
We don't suffer very much in America today.

00:48:18.599 --> 00:48:21.359
Not saying that it's gonna change tomorrow,

00:48:21.359 --> 00:48:22.979
but I'm just simply saying,

00:48:23.859 --> 00:48:25.379
we're probably not gonna have the freedoms

00:48:25.379 --> 00:48:26.959
that we have today forever.

00:48:28.559 --> 00:48:33.559
Things are changing rapidly, rapidly changing.

00:48:37.299 --> 00:48:40.139
We gotta be in a place where we can say as Paul said,

00:48:40.139 --> 00:48:43.359
for I know whom I have believed

00:48:43.359 --> 00:48:46.679
and I am persuaded that he is able.

00:48:47.659 --> 00:48:51.639
Listen, this morning, trials are to be expected.

00:48:52.899 --> 00:48:56.500
They're gonna be varied, but they're to be expected.

00:48:56.500 --> 00:48:57.699
But I want you to know this morning

00:48:57.699 --> 00:49:01.459
that with the help of God and for his glory,

00:49:01.459 --> 00:49:05.279
we can endure through the trials.

00:49:06.659 --> 00:49:08.859
I don't know what trials you have right now,

00:49:09.739 --> 00:49:12.479
but I know that God knows all about it.

00:49:12.479 --> 00:49:15.639
And I know that God has a purpose in it.

00:49:15.639 --> 00:49:18.659
Paul said as he wrote to the people in Philippi,

00:49:18.659 --> 00:49:20.019
the things that happen unto me

00:49:20.019 --> 00:49:23.619
happen for the furtherance of the gospel.

00:49:23.619 --> 00:49:26.019
There might be a trial that you're facing today

00:49:26.899 --> 00:49:29.659
because somebody needs to hear the gospel.

00:49:29.659 --> 00:49:31.399
And the only way they're gonna hear the gospel

00:49:31.399 --> 00:49:34.819
is because you have a trial

00:49:34.819 --> 00:49:37.500
that's gonna bring you into the office

00:49:37.500 --> 00:49:38.879
of a medical professional,

00:49:38.879 --> 00:49:41.859
or you have a trial that's going to have some technician

00:49:41.859 --> 00:49:44.819
have to come to your home to take care of some whatever.

00:49:45.699 --> 00:49:47.039
You say, I don't have time for this.

00:49:47.039 --> 00:49:48.099
I don't have money for this.

00:49:48.099 --> 00:49:49.539
I don't have whatever.

00:49:49.539 --> 00:49:52.619
But the reality, listen, God knows who he can trust.

00:49:54.059 --> 00:49:57.619
And he gives us, listen, he gave Paul opportunities

00:49:57.619 --> 00:50:01.059
that only came because of the trials.

00:50:01.059 --> 00:50:04.299
Only.

00:50:04.299 --> 00:50:08.179
How did Festus and Agrippa, how did those guys hear the gospel?

00:50:08.179 --> 00:50:10.419
Because Paul was imprisoned.

00:50:10.419 --> 00:50:13.659
How were there some people saved that were of the household of Caesar that Paul writes

00:50:13.659 --> 00:50:15.939
about in Philippi?

00:50:15.939 --> 00:50:16.939
Because Paul was imprisoned.

00:50:16.939 --> 00:50:23.339
And there are some people that heard the gospel while he was in prison and got saved.

00:50:23.339 --> 00:50:25.099
Praise God.

00:50:25.099 --> 00:50:30.499
I don't know what trials you have, but I know the God that we serve.

00:50:30.499 --> 00:50:33.539
And I know that trials are to be expected.

00:50:33.539 --> 00:50:38.619
And with His help and for His glory, we can endure.

00:50:38.619 --> 00:50:43.619
Paul says, you want me to boast, you want me to glory?

00:50:43.619 --> 00:50:46.499
I'm going to glory about those things concerning my infirmities.

00:50:46.499 --> 00:50:47.499
Why?

00:50:47.499 --> 00:50:52.819
So that God is exalted, so that God is glorified.

00:50:52.819 --> 00:50:53.819
Let's pray.

00:50:53.819 --> 00:50:54.819
Father, we love You.

00:50:54.819 --> 00:50:56.059
We thank You so much for loving us.

00:50:56.059 --> 00:50:57.859
We thank You for the Word.

00:50:57.859 --> 00:51:00.099
We thank You for the truth.

00:51:00.099 --> 00:51:01.899
We thank You for the testimony.

00:51:01.899 --> 00:51:06.579
And God, we thank You for the trials.

00:51:06.579 --> 00:51:10.019
I know we often don't think that way.

00:51:10.019 --> 00:51:17.220
God help us to be thankful for the trials, knowing that You have a purpose and a plan

00:51:17.220 --> 00:51:19.419
and that You do all things well.

00:51:19.419 --> 00:51:27.579
God, I pray that You would help those, some that are going through some trials, some that

00:51:27.579 --> 00:51:30.699
are intense, some that have been long.

00:51:30.699 --> 00:51:32.739
God, would You help them this morning?

00:51:32.739 --> 00:51:38.819
Would You give them the hope that they need, the grace that they need?

00:51:38.819 --> 00:51:43.939
Would You help them to endure by Your power and for Your glory?

00:51:43.939 --> 00:51:51.419
God, I pray that if there's one here that's not saved, I pray that You'd help them to

00:51:51.419 --> 00:51:54.779
understand their need for Christ.

00:51:54.779 --> 00:51:59.500
I pray, Lord, that in this moment of invitation that You'd have Your will and way.

00:51:59.500 --> 00:52:04.659
You'd help us to do business with You, Lord, that we'd be doers and not hearers.

00:52:04.659 --> 00:52:06.500
We'll give You the glory for all that You'll do.

00:52:06.500 --> 00:52:07.899
For it's in Christ's name we pray.

00:52:07.899 --> 00:52:10.059
Would You stand with me?

00:52:10.059 --> 00:52:11.059
Heads are bowed, eyes are closed.

00:52:11.059 --> 00:52:13.860
Kimberly's going to play quietly on the piano.

00:52:13.860 --> 00:52:15.259
As she does, the altar is open.

